In a medium pot, bring the water and chicken broth to a boil. Add the spaghetti pasta, and cook until al dente. Drain well. In a large skillet saute onion in olive oil until tender. Add chicken, mushrooms, 1 ounce of Cheddar cheese, flour, and cooked spaghetti. Mix well. Pour mixture into a 2 quart baking dish. Top dish with remaining ounce of Cheddar cheese and almonds. Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven (175 degrees C) for 30 to 40 minutes.